<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AFC 98904 - Engine Road Draft Tube Extension</stitle>
    <afc id="afc98904">
        <afcnum>98904</afcnum>
        <afcdate>December, 1998</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subject>Engine Road Draft Tube Extension</subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3000
                    <daterange>
                        <enddate>03/28/1998</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This AFC applies to AmTran 3000RE bus chassis with V8 engine built prior to April 28, 1998 with a
                    12 inch road draft extension or no road draft extension.
                </para>
                <para>Engine crankcase vapors exiting the road draft tube and re-entering the engine compartment on
                    3000RE bus chassis can contribute to radiator CAC (charge air cooler) plugging. In July 1997 AmTran
                    started installing a 12 inch hose to extend the road draft tube. It has been determined that adding
                    a 24 inch hose extension to the road draft tube will decrease the amount of contamination (fouling)
                    of the CAC and direct the oil vapor away from the engine compartment.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
